   An expensive pair of SWIMshorts

   I bought but returned my pair of 2-in-1 swimshorts: they were too short
   for my liking. I hoped the design was something like a pair of
   boardshorts (just above knee length; I am 1.77m), so that I could
   actually wear them as regular shorts. However, they only reached the
   middle of my thighs, meaning they actually looked like swimshorts.
   As such, these swimshorts are perfect: stretchy fabric, stylish look,
   super comfortable inner trunks, hidden zippered pocket and water
   repellent fabric just as advertised (although I wonder whether that
   effect wears off after repeated washing). However, I feel I could only
   wear these as swimshorts, and that makes them a very expensive buy.
   If you don't mind wearing short shorts, these are actually 2-in-1
   shorts. However, for people who like longer shorts, these can only
   serve as (expensive) swimshorts.

